<br>
My suggestion would be Seer.  Now that may not sound right to some people (for blowing up things Arcanist works better) but let me tell you something, I've done extensive research on wizardry and wizards ARE typically prophets and advisors.  <br>
<br>
The average wizard story usually focuses on the student, not the master as learning the craft is far more interesting as the master wizard is so far beyond conventional comprehension everything he says or does is magical, this serves to educate the reader as well as give the reader a feeling of &quot;travelling&quot; the world of magic.<br>
<br>
The master wizard however, such as Merlin is most often seen as a Seer or advisor (advisor to the once and future king Arthur), the master wizard's job is too guide the less worldly, however for those who choose the Dark path, the same holds true.  A point I made in a paper I wrote (and may publish here in a few months if I don't get word back soon), is that evil/good for wizards is a misconstrued concept.  There are no good or evil wizards, just wizards with good or bad intentions.  Point being, the masterful wizard is still a prophet and teacher, so my vote goes to Seer or some variation (note, druids crystal balls and tarot cards are a whole 'nother matter and that aspect is not seen in EQ hence the title still belongs to us).<br>
<br>
Failing all else Arcanist works too.<br>
<br>
Yaldin<br>
60 Sorceror<br>
Karana Server<br>
